enhanced_by.reason: The region method provides the AWS region required for constructing the ARN.
The accountId method provides the AWS account ID required for constructing the ARN.
The appName method provides the application name required for constructing the ARN.
The randHex method provides a random hexadecimal string required for constructing the ARN.
The region method must be invoked before albTargetGroupARN to ensure the correct region is used.
The accountId method must be invoked before albTargetGroupARN to ensure the correct account ID is used.
The appName method must be invoked before albTargetGroupARN to ensure the correct application name is used.
The randHex method must be invoked before albTargetGroupARN to ensure a valid random hexadecimal string is generated.
